        <item>
        <title>Obsidian as Markdown Editor for Hugo</title>
        <link>https://1ar.io/p/obsidian-as-markdown-editor-for-hugo/</link>
        <pubDate>Sun, 15 Oct 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        
        <guid>https://1ar.io/p/obsidian-as-markdown-editor-for-hugo/</guid>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;handling md files for hugo with obsidian seems like a good idea&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;settings need changing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;in Editor:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;properties in document - &lt;code&gt;visible&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;img src=&#34;https://1ar.io/post/Obsidian%20as%20Markdown%20Editor%20for%20Hugo/Pasted%20Graphic%205.png&#34;
	
	
	
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
	
&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;in Files and Links:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;folder to create new notes - &lt;code&gt;in the folder specified below&lt;/code&gt; - &lt;code&gt;post&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;new link format - &lt;code&gt;absolute path in vault&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;use [[Wikilinks]] - &lt;code&gt;disabled&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;default location for new attachments - &lt;code&gt;same folder as current file&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://1ar.io/post/Obsidian%20as%20Markdown%20Editor%20for%20Hugo/Pasted%20Graphic%204.png&#34;
	
	
	
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
	
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
        </item>
        <item>
        <title>Snapping and moving windows on macOS with shortcuts</title>
        <link>https://1ar.io/p/snapping-and-moving-windows-on-macos-with-shortcuts/</link>
        <pubDate>Sun, 15 Oct 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        
        <guid>https://1ar.io/p/snapping-and-moving-windows-on-macos-with-shortcuts/</guid>
        <description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While you can use 3rd party tools like &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://apps.apple.com/de/app/magnet/id441258766?l=en&amp;amp;mt=12&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;Magnet&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://rectangleapp.com/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;Rectangle&lt;/a&gt; to snap windows to the sides or move things around, you can achieve basic keyboard interaction without any apps at all.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://1ar.io/post/Snapping%20and%20moving%20windows%20on%20macOS%20with%20shortcut/snapping.png&#34;
	
	
	
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
	
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
